  "text": "In the present study, a self-etching primer (ED Primer II) was used. Gluma did not contribute to improve the bond strength, because Gluma has a better mechanism of action when used to etch-and-rinse approach, when occurs the rewet or the restablishment of the collagen fibrils [CITATION_1] . Regarding the SEM analysis, the micrographs showed semi-closed dentinal tubules, but it did not form a thick coating, and 50% mixed failures (between adhesive and cohesive in resin cement), 30% adhesive and 20% cohesive failures in resin cement failures (Figure 2 ).",
